A green cursor blinks on the terminal; 2,847 logged “green” strings fluoresce like trapped fireflies.  
In the concrete carpark, three surgical-masked figures lock into perfect 120° triangles, green gloves reflecting oily rainbows.  
The backward-driving car—empty, screaming tires—recedes yet never vanishes, always reappearing in the rearview rectangle.  
Heat lingers on the saved car key; the server fans keep whispering the same tire-screech loop, promising the dreamer will be back.
